{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_59","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc 'nl -ba harness/checklist.md'","aggregated_output":"     1\t# MiniLang LSP Harness Checklist\n     2\t\n     3\t1. `encodeMessage` must return a valid JSON-RPC framed payload where every response starts with `Content-Length: <byteLength>`, followed by `\\r\\n\\r\\n`, and the JSON body equals `JSON.stringify(message)`.\n     4\t2. `MessageBuffer.push` must accept fragmented input and return `[]` for incomplete frames, then return exactly each fully reconstructed message object in order once enough bytes arrive.\n     5\t3. `MessageBuffer.push` must decode multiple concatenated frames from streamed input and emit all complete messages in sequence.\n     6\t4. `MiniLangServer.handle({method:'initialize'})` must return `jsonrpc: '2.0'`, the same `id`, and capabilities containing `textDocumentSync`, `completionProvider`, `definitionProvider`, and `hoverProvider`.\n     7\t5. `MiniLangServer.handle({method:'shutdown'})` must return `{jsonrpc: '2.0', id, result: null}` and `MiniLangServer.handle({method:'exit'})` must return `null` without throwing.\n     8\t6. On `didOpen`, the server must publish diagnostics for both undefined symbol references and function arity mismatches and also store those diagnostics in `getDiagnostics(uri)`.\n     9\t7. On malformed input such as brace/syntax errors, parsing must still recover and still publish semantic diagnostics it can compute (including undefined and arity issues when present).\n    10\t8. On `didChange`, document content must be updated incrementally and published diagnostics must replace the previous set for that URI (old diagnostics that no longer apply are removed).\n    11\t9. Completion responses must only include items matching the current token prefix at cursor position, and must include symbols available in the current scope (not leaking symbols outside scope).\n    12\t10. Completion items must expose function signature information for function symbols (for example parameter list in `label`/`detail`/`insertText`).\n    13\t11. Go-to-definition must resolve symbol declarations, and when a name exists both locally and elsewhere, it must choose the local-scope declaration.\n    14\t12. Hover must return symbol/function documentation text for the symbol at cursor and include function signature text for function symbols.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
